originalText.text: DO NOT PARK HERE UNDER ANY CIRCUMSTANCES. Another garage under the same management badly scratched my car and continues to deny it despite overwhelming evidence.  So slimy.  Avoid them at all costs.

originalText.text: Worst experience got a spothero parking reservation  for $17.95 on Jan 1 for around 6:30pm to 12am,  I got there after 7pm because of traffic, anyway the guy at the parking very rude not welcoming not nice, I told him I got a parking reservation and I open the app he told me I will need it later, after I come back, I came back around 10:30 it was close and someone else was waiting once I gave him my ticket he open grated the guy this guy gave him cash and then left in his blue BMW after that he scan my ticket and told me my sporthero reservation is not working, my total came to $42.00 it would only deduct what I paid, it didn’t make sense he was charging me the difference of $25, I ask why? Even the sign at garage entrance  has a $21.12 all day special, very rude said I don’t know just paid please call spothero and they will give you a refund he said , I was not going to paid but my husband did, my two girls were very tired, after my husband paid he handles me the receipt in the car I realize is not my ticket the enter time was 3:09pm and the blue BMW as description for a car, I do see what he did he kept the cash and charge me for the other car ticket, I am contacting NY Consumer DCWP. Be aware of this business!!

originalText.text: SCAM ALERT, I bought tickets for radio city music hall and reserved parking on parkwhiz app. App says till 12am but employee says they close at 11 and if I stay passed that I will have to come back tomorrow and pay $82 to get my car back. Employee even insisted that I cancel my reservation and go to another parking lot that's 24 hours.

originalText.text: They make reservations when they don't have spaces.  They don't tell you until you arrive.  The ramps are terrible.  The worker wasn't terrible but he certainly was not good.  So, this place managed to be inadequate in every area you hope a parking garage will do well.
